uality of the education).  They distract other student from obsorbing what is being taught, (which lowers the quality of the education).  They often instill fear in other weaker students, (which lowers the quality of education).   Bottom line is, if you want to send your kids to a good public school, you have to move to a wealthier, good neighborhood that doesn't have any bad section that can send those kids to your school. It is easier to send your kids to private school where the majority of parents that are paying for school, care enough to make sure they have good kids! "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="888" language="en" documentId="3852" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Someone (Simmon Fan)" date="Aug 29, 2013 6:25PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="37" thumbsDown="0" origId="3852" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="888"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>